messageBody:
Right, but as you'll notice, read made the loops of #29 / #31 slightly
more elliptical than #35 / #37. I simply propose to move the joining
points of the latter two and emphasize the ellitical nature of the
former two.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, Chuck Peck <chuck091956@y...> wrote:
> From a hand writen stand point, I form #37 & #37
> closer to what #29 & #31 looks like. This allows the
> it to connect better.
>
> http://calendar.yahoo.com
